Most of the sketches in this directory need a couple of additional libraries for OSC and MIDI support.

Linux
=====
OSC
---
OSC support depends on pyOSC, which can be obtained from:
http://trac.v2.nl/wiki/pyOSC
Installation instructions are included in the package

MIDI
----
MIDI support depends on pyPortMidi, which can be obtained from:
http://nosuch.com/tjt/nosuchsoft/
Steps to install:
1) Make sure you have pyrex installed - it is packaged for almost all major distibutions.  Run python pyrexc --version to check whether it is already installed
2) Grab the package which fits with your version of python (2.4 or 2.5)
3) Unzip the archive
4) Run python setup.py install as root from within the extracted archive

OSX
===
OSC
---
OSC support depends on pyOSC, which can be obtained from:
http://trac.v2.nl/wiki/pyOSC
Installation instructions are included in the package

MIDI
----
MIDI support depends on pyPortMidi, which can be obtained from:
http://nosuch.com/tjt/nosuchsoft/
Steps to install:
1) Make sure you have pyrex installed - it is available from Darwinports as py-pyrex.  Run python pyrexc --version to check whether it is already installed
2) Grab the package which fits with your version of python (2.4 or 2.5)
3) Unzip the archive
4) Run python setup.py install as root from within the extracted archive

Windows
=======
OSC
---
OSC support depends on pyOSC, which can be obtained from:
http://trac.v2.nl/wiki/pyOSC
Steps to install:
1) Grap the latest zip of pyOSC
2) Unzip the archive
3) Make sure the python executable is in your system PATH
4) Go Start=>Run=>cmd
5) Change directory to the extracted archive, and run python setup.py install

MIDI
----
MIDI support depends on pyPortMidi, which can be obtained from:
http://nosuch.com/tjt/nosuchsoft/
Steps to install:
1) Grab the package which fits with your version of python (2.4 or 2.5)
2) Unzip the archive
3) Copy pypm.pyd to your python lib\site-package directory
